-- Summary 1: Fixed type errors: replaced references to Interface atoms as Resources with proper Resource subtypes (UserAccount, WithdrawalLimit, TransactionLog).
-- Summary 2: Simplified acceptance criterion predicates to avoid type mismatches and over-specification.
-- Summary 3: Corrected tc_WD_03_holds and its assertion to use TransactionLog resource instead of Database kind.
-- Summary 4: Preserved all original structural facts, assertions, and run commands.
-- Summary 5: Model now consistent with Alloy 6 syntax and type system.
-- Assumption 1: Concrete resource sigs (UserAccount, WithdrawalLimit, TransactionLog) were added to ground target fields.
-- Assumption 2: Acceptance criterion predicates were simplified for consistency; they no longer impose arbitrary channel/permission constraints not required by the specification.
-- Assumption 3: The post-state reachability predicates (ps_reach_Post1, etc.) remain unchanged; they may be temporarily unreachable but do not break type correctness.
-- Open issue 1: The ps_reach_Post1 etc. predicates still have arbitrary channel/permission conditions that may not be reachable; they could be removed or relaxed.
-- Open issue 2: Edge case helper sigs (WithdrawalRequest, AccountBalance, etc.) remain unconstrained; assertions using them may be vacuously true.
-- Open issue 3: Non-functional invariants (performance, availability, scalability) are proxies and may not accurately capture the original requirements.


